Hello! We are glad to have you here! We are a new faction called "
The Undead Warriors[D.E.A.D]
" and we mostly hang out, play together in-game, and mostly, have fun! If you are looking for a faction that is open for everyone who is good at PvP or who wants to become a good PvP player, has a friendly community, and is serious, this faction is for you! Benefits: 1. Lots of fun 2. Friendly community to make friends 3. Offers protection 4. Giveaways 5. Helping each other for grinding money! 6. Wars and Raids! Requirements to join: 1. Don't be toxic,a little bit of toxicity can be tolerated 2. Respect others opinions 3. Do not judge others based on their beliefs, opinions, and race! 4. No hacking/spamming 5. Always report toxic members/hackers 6. Stay loyal to the faction and never backstab your comrades! 7. Always obey orders! 8. BE REALLY ACTIVE! 9. WEAR UNIFORM Have a great stay! Reminder: This server is for EVERYONE WHO IS SUPER ACTIVE,GOOD AT PVP,AND WHO CAN LISTEN TO ORDERS so there are no hard requirements. Anyone is welcome to join who thinks he/she has decent PvP skills! Also, our faction is brand new so we are still developing and not finished yet. If you have suggestions that will make us do better, please let us know. FOR THE UNDEAD Thank you alot ! What is Troll Wild West‚ùì Troll Wild West is a faction for TWW which doesn't take itself so seriously, now we aren't gonna lie and say stuff like we have the best players in the game or something but if you would like to improve your skills we can help you with that. Events We usually host like 1 event a day such as: raids, wars, practice, free for all and more! Requirements You don't need to be the best at pvp to join the faction but you need good aim because we can teach you other stuff. -Have good aim -Good weapons (preferably not a spam shotgun) -Good horse (Mustang is a recommendation but a 10k horse isn't needed) -Having a mic and talking in vc is preferred More stuff Getting ranked up is really easy if you are active. We are always looking for more high ranks, active members and skilled players. Most of us talk in vc alot and joining vc is a requirement but you don't have to talk if you don't feel like it but talking is still preferred. Stats Ingame members: ~50 Average rally count: ~4 - 10 Links Clan Trailer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6bjBSJ12AnY Discord Invite: https://discord.gg/RnBcwURDwE If you would like to get good at pvp we can actually train you and get you really good no matter what skill level you are

We aren't some ragtag bunch of players or a huge gang with terrible organization. We're not just some ordinary faction either. We are a team, working together to make cash and have fun. We believe in hard work and skill. Our ranking system is not based on how many times you suck up to your superiors (like some other factions), but on merit, contribution, and skill. We also believe in learning. As long as you're willing to learn, we have experienced players who can teach you every aspect of the game, and scheduled events and trainings regularly. If you're lacking in skill, don't worry! We'll help you get better. What do we offer? - Guidance from experienced players - An active, growing community - Assistance with grinding - An opportunity to rise to the top - Events and Trainings - Frequent Giveaways - Fun and Profit Requirements - Unwavering loyalty to the faction - Be reasonably active (play at least twice a week, minimum) - 13+ (otherwise, why are you even on discord?) - Knowledge of all the game mechanics - Participation and Contribution to the faction - Follow the rules, and respect all faction members - Willingness to learn - No Toxicity APPLY TODAY! WE ARE THE MUSKETEERS All for one, one for all! We are the Musketeers, a faction of experienced players dedicated to making money and having fun in the process. We aren't some ragtag bunch of players or a huge gang with terrible organization. We're not just some ordinary faction either. We are a team, working together to make cash and have fun. We believe in hard work and skill. Our ranking system is not based on how many times you suck up to your superiors (like some other factions), but on merit, contribution, and skill. We also believe in learning. As long as you're willing to learn, we have experienced players who can teach you every aspect of the game, and scheduled events and trainings regularly. If you're lacking in skill, don't worry! We'll help you get better. What do we offer? - Guidance from experienced players - An active, growing community - Assistance with grinding - An opportunity to rise to the top - Events and Trainings - Frequent Giveaways - Fun and Profit Requirements - Unwavering loyalty to the faction - Be reasonably active (play at least twice a week, minimum) - 13+ (otherwise, why are you even on discord?) - Knowledge of all the game mechanics - Participation and Contribution to the faction - Follow the rules, and respect all faction members - Willingness to learn - No Toxicity APPLY TODAY! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! MrFluffyLion 20-Dec-21 08:56 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. MrFluffyLion 22-Dec-21 06:27 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. "THE UNITED STATES MARSHALS ARE NOW RECRUITING"
+ NOTICE: For the first week of January, January 1st through Janurary 8th, The Application requirement will be waived to all incoming recruits. Take advantage of the oppertunity while you can.
We are the United States Marshals Service. We pride ourselves on being an elite fighting force that can and has faced whatever has come our way. Through our skill, leadership, communication, and tactics we have fought and won battles against the odds, and put up stalwart resistance against enemies that outnumber us 3:1, and we have won every war we have fought. Our selective application process has allowed us to admit only those worthy of calling themselves a Marshal into our ranks. So tell us. Do you have what it takes to become a United States Marshal?
[Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications in game. - Must have a good horse. (Mustang or American Quarterhorse encouraged) - Decent at combat - A IQ at or above 100. - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders quickly and efficiently.
+ Benefits:
+ Free Black Market Supplies + A good group of friends. + Daily Patrols. + Joining a faction with the capability of holding two forts at once while they are being assaulted + An excellent environment to hone your skills. + Tier 3 Nitro Boost Rewards + A faction undefeated in war.
[Wars]
+ Battle of Pinewood - USMS vs Eternal Raiders 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 7 USMS. 7 ER. + Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Falcone Crime Syndicate 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS. 6 FCS + Battle of Callahan Manor - USMS vs Piedmont Tribe, USMS Victory.
[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs + Third Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Bleeding Falcons. Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 5 OC, BF, Varied others.
Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

We believe in hard work and skill. Our ranking system is not based on how many times you suck up to your superiors (like some other factions), but on merit, contribution, and skill. We also believe in learning. As long as you're willing to learn, we have experienced players who can teach you every aspect of the game, and scheduled events and trainings regularly. "Tell me and I‚Äôll forget. Show me, and I may not remember. Involve me, and I‚Äôll understand." II. In Comanche you are not just a number, you are a member meaning your presence is noticed, and your voice is heard. Everyone serves an equal opportunity here, to drive as a united force strengthens our bonds with one another. "It is better to have less thunder in the mouth and more lightning in the hand." III. Choose Your Path: The journey will be rigorous, but you will never fight a battle alone. To join Comanche is to join another family, no back is left vulnerable and our eyes watch out for one another. MrFluffyLion 07-Jan-22 04:00 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: ‚Ä¢ An active group. ‚Ä¢ Fun and friendly community. ‚Ä¢ Fun and engaging events ‚Ä¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. ‚Ä¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "You have to have skill to live." Requirements: ‚Ä¢ Wear a tribal uniform and accessory. ‚Ä¢ Respect each other and the rules. ‚Ä¢ Have a tribal weapon. ‚Ä¢ Have a decent horse. ‚Ä¢ Be active. " and we mostly hang out, play together in-game, and mostly, have fun! If you are looking for a faction that is open for everyone who is good at PvP or who wants to become a good PvP player, has a friendly community, and is serious, this faction is for you! Benefits: 1. Lots of fun 2. Friendly community to make friends 3. Offers protection 4. Giveaways 5. Helping each other for grinding money! 6. Wars and Raids! Requirements to join: 1. Don't be toxic,a little bit of toxicity can be tolerated 2. Respect others opinions 3. Do not judge others based on their beliefs, opinions, and race! 4. No hacking/spamming 5. Always report toxic members/hackers 6. Stay loyal to the faction and never backstab your comrades! 7. Always obey orders! 8. BE REALLY ACTIVE! 9. WEAR UNIFORM Have a great stay! Note: This server is for EVERYONE WHO IS SUPER ACTIVE,GOOD AT PVP,AND WHO CAN LISTEN TO ORDERS so there are no hard requirements. Anyone is welcome to join who thinks he/she has decent PvP skills,and if he/she passes the tryouts,then they will officially be a faction member! Also, our faction is brand new so we are still developing and not finished yet. If you have suggestions that will make us do better, please let us know. "FROM THE DEPTHS OF HELL" Thank you alot ! MrFluffyLion 09-Jan-22 03:35 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: ‚Ä¢ An active group. ‚Ä¢ Fun and friendly community. ‚Ä¢ Fun and engaging events ‚Ä¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. ‚Ä¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "You have to have skill to live." Requirements: ‚Ä¢ Wear a tribal uniform and accessory. ‚Ä¢ Respect each other and the rules. ‚Ä¢ Have a tribal weapon. ‚Ä¢ Have a decent horse. ‚Ä¢ Be active. PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: ‚Ä¢ An active group. ‚Ä¢ Fun and friendly community. ‚Ä¢ Fun and engaging events ‚Ä¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. ‚Ä¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "You have to have skill to live." Requirements: ‚Ä¢ Wear a tribal uniform and accessory. ‚Ä¢ Respect each other and the rules. ‚Ä¢ Have a tribal weapon. ‚Ä¢ Have a decent horse. ‚Ä¢ Be active. PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Mysterio 16-Jan-22 06:48 PM
The Revolutionary Confederation is a fictional organized resurgence of paramilitary pioneers and frontiersmen alike, who have denied the rapidly growing mechanical and agrarian ways of society. We thrive by the organization in principles and ethics, centered on the idea of "liberty through unity" by associations of justice and crime. Through our goal in spreading influence of freedom and salvation, the Confederation and it's pioneers shall embark a new path of liberty, for we all are one.
The Confederation is made up of various assemblies, each led by a Chief Major. People may join multiple assemblies and attend events for any assembly. These assemblies specialize and host events in their specific role. One assembly may specialize in mining, another in training, etc. Anybody can form a assembly as long as they get approved by the Chairman and meet the requirements! This makes our faction very friendly to new players. There are also events faction-wide events.
Requirements: 1. Faction Uniform (Less restrictive when promoted) 2. VC for events (Mic not required) 3. Fun! Notes:
- The Revolutionary Confederation is a new faction! Many of opportunities and beginnings.
>
- Ranks are progressive, if you're active by attending events, you'll eventually climb the ranks! You don't need to keep track of your attendance, as we will.
>
- We are temporarily seeking HRs, as in our organization, we are looking to find people wanting to build a foundation! NOT necessarily free ranking
>
- We are not like many other factions in terms of organization and ranks, and want to be as unique as possible while maintaining simplicity and overall fun! We are player friendly so if you're inexperienced, we welcome you!
Motto: "Liberty Through Unity!" Diplomacy: You are either with us, or against us https://discord.gg/mJfrKMGqWX

MrFluffyLion 18-Jan-22 05:07 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! We are the United States Marshals Service. [Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications - Must have a 3 Star Horse - Good at combat - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders.
+ Benefits:
+ A good group of friends. + An environment to hone your skills. + Tier 3 Nitro Boost Rewards + A faction undefeated in war.
[Wars]

[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs + Third Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Bleeding Falcons. Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

The Wild West Community Hall Community Hall information Purpose I wanted to create a new faction hub, when i started on the server for it i came up with an idea to make a sort of "mall". I wanted people to be closer together in TWW without being divided in different servers. This server will have everything you want in tww, from new reports to movie studios, and always open to new suggestions. More information will be given in the ‚îÇ„Ä¢reaction-roles channel and every Districts information channel. Districts Districts are the areas made out for peoples interests, like a Library Category for people that want to read about TWW Lore. Award Districts for people that want to know who the best "player" is in different categories of gameplay. Different people have been elected to lead these districts, TabletID leads the shop districts, Dann owns the News and Studio districts, Farwest owns the server and helps lead all the districts, Jin X helps to lead the districts as well. More District leaders will be elected in the future. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- More information TWW community hall is a great community with great moderation! We have nice members and a very active community. Extra The Wild West Community Hall was founded by Farwest on 1/3/2022. We welcome everyone here and hit 100 members in under 24 hours! Join TWW community hall to make new friends and enjoy a great community with a inside newspaper, shops, and more! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! MrFluffyLion 23-Jan-22 08:45 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: ‚Ä¢ An active group. ‚Ä¢ Fun and friendly community. ‚Ä¢ Fun and engaging events ‚Ä¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. ‚Ä¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "You have to have skill to live." Requirements: ‚Ä¢ Wear a tribal uniform and accessory. ‚Ä¢ Respect each other and the rules. ‚Ä¢ Have a tribal weapon. ‚Ä¢ Have a decent horse. ‚Ä¢ Be active. PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: ‚Ä¢ An active group. ‚Ä¢ Fun and friendly community. ‚Ä¢ Fun and engaging events ‚Ä¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. ‚Ä¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "You have to have skill to live." Requirements: ‚Ä¢ Wear a tribal uniform and accessory. ‚Ä¢ Respect each other and the rules. ‚Ä¢ Have a tribal weapon. ‚Ä¢ Have a decent horse. ‚Ä¢ Be active. Faction Diplomacy Hub Hello, welcome to the TWW faction hub, this is a new discord server and it is merely a test. The TWW faction community has evolved into a very toxic and competitive place, we aim to improve diplomacy and begin a middlemen in arguments when war seems the only option. We also aid to provide benefits such as a moderator made diplomacy channel (you tell us the news we quickly phrase it) so you can control F whenever you want news for a faction. Benefits We offer a "battle request" system where if you are a verified nation you can follow a format to try and schedule an official battle. We offer an organized faction news area where we have several different faction updates for people who dont wish to be in 100 servers to stay in tune with current faction politics, these are organized off importance, shitpost amount, and respect within the community. We offer a diplomacy section of the discord which will look something like this. You dm me or moderators info and we make a "diplomacy message" We offer a middleman diplomacy service, a faction can apply for a monitered negotiation with another faction, if both accept and the negotations go to hell then the moderators can moderate the discussion, end negotiations, or threaten to remove a factions verification within the server. If negotiations fail, we can try to help. New server, no factions as of now im still trying to get some. If you own a faction and wanna try to make the community more cooperative give it a try. https://discord.gg/CCkE78q8a2 (edited)

MrFluffyLion 04-Feb-22 02:19 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on!
